---
source: crates/wxctl/tests/panel_snapshots.rs
expression: "run(&[\"explain\", \"agent\"], \"80\", \"never\", \"\")"
---

  agent   watsonx Orchestrate - saas, software
  id field - id

  | Endpoints
    create   POST     /v1/orchestrate/agents
    get      GET      /v1/orchestrate/agents/{id}
    list     GET      /v1/orchestrate/agents
    update   PATCH    /v1/orchestrate/agents/{id}
    delete   DELETE   /v1/orchestrate/agents/{id}

  | Fields   (required first)
    name                          string          required            Body
    description                   string          required            Body
    style                         string          required            Body
    llm                           string          required            Body
    display_name                  string          optional            Body
    instructions                  string          optional            Body
    llm_config                    object          optional            Body
    structured_output             object          optional            Body
    hidden                        boolean         optional            Body
    hide_reasoning                boolean         optional            Body
    sync_tool_flow_interactions   boolean         optional            Body
    context_access_enabled        boolean         optional            Body
    tools                         array<string>   optional            Body
    toolkits                      array<string>   optional            Body
    collaborators                 array<string>   optional            Body
    knowledge_base                array<string>   optional            Body
    glossary                      array<string>   optional            Body
    guidelines                    array<object>   optional            Body
    connection_ids                array<string>   optional            Body
    context_variables             array<string>   optional            Body
    additional_properties         object          optional            Body
    chat_with_docs                object          optional            Body
    tags                          array<string>   optional            Body
    id                            string          computed   locked   Computed
    agent_mapping                 object          computed            Computed
    environments                  array           computed            Computed
    tenant_id                     string          computed   locked   Computed
    created_by                    string          computed   locked   Computed
    created_on                    timestamp       computed   locked   Computed
    updated_by                    string          computed            Computed
    updated_at                    timestamp       computed            Computed
    deleted_by                    string          computed            Computed
    deleted_at                    timestamp       computed            Computed

  | Dependencies
    llm             -->  ${model.<ref_name>}   optional
    tools           -->  ${tool.<ref_name>}   optional
    toolkits        -->  ${toolkit.<ref_name>}   optional
    collaborators   -->  ${agent.<ref_name>}   optional
    knowledge_base  -->  ${knowledge_base.<ref_name>}   optional

  | Notes
    * Agent `style` controls reasoning: `default` is standard conversational, `react` enables ReAct (Reasoning + Acting) for step-by-step problem solving, `planner` enables advanced multi-step task decomposition.
    * Tools are referenced using `${tool.<ref_name>}` syntax, collaborators using `${agent.<ref_name>}`, and knowledge bases using `${knowledge_base.<ref_name>}`.
    * The `llm` field accepts either a `${model.<ref_name>}` reference or a plain string value (e.g., `groq/openai/gpt-oss-120b`). Plain values create no dependency.
    * The `description` field serves as the agent's system prompt and defines its core purpose, behavior, and capabilities.
    * Guidelines provide behavioral rules with `condition` (when the guideline applies) and `action` (what the agent should do).
    * `additional_properties` supports `icon` (SVG string), `starter_prompts` (suggested conversation starters), and `welcome_content` (initial greeting).

  | Authoring
    envelope   A config is one or more YAML documents separated by `---`. Each has top-level `kind` and `ref_name`, then the fields below at the top level (not nested under `spec`).
    ref_name   Unique handle for this resource within the config. Used to reference it from other resources; stripped before the API call (not a schema field).
    reference  Reference another resource by its ref_name: `${<kind>.<ref_name>}` resolves to its id, `${<kind>.<ref_name>.<field>}` to a specific field. Values resolve late, at plan/apply time.
